full_text:
This is exactly why I left that group. This email and the last big one he sent you were so laced with hate and ignorant statements that it opened my eyes to his truest colors. Couple points this &quot;researcher&quot; never took the time to learn. Correct me if I am wrong, but doesn&#39;t white noise as applied to your boxes mean the electronic noise coming off of junction/diode section of the RVG and not an actual sound? And as for using a 469 tuner as the tuning module of the box, who the hell thinks that is using a &quot;shack hack&quot; in the box? When you apply voltage tuning using either RVG or linear sweep, you are bypassing the internal tuning of the radio, hence completely bypassing the circuitry that makes it a &quot;shack hack&quot;. And since you aren&#39;t using the controller board of the 469, how the hell does shack hack become relevant? Just because it shares the same model number as the shack hack, when it is used as a tuning module in a box, then whether it is hacked or not is completely irrelevant. 

I am no expert, but I was able to build a linear &quot;box&quot; according to your plans. I found a simple triangle generator and used it to VT the headless 469. It never left the breadboard, as I was basically doing it for challenge, and I could never stabilize the sweep voltage. This wasn&#39;t a reflection on your design, but my inexperience with electronics.If I was better at it, I could probably get the thing stabilized, but just getting one sweep out of it made my head hurt. I guess what I am saying, is your help during my building process was irreplaceable and I couldn&#39;t have done it without it. People appreciate what you do.

I am not an expert, just a lay researcher, and the busy pace of other life has relegated me to &quot;enthusiast&quot; here lately. I do keep up though, and I have been real encouraged to see that you have been open to doing radio shows and going to events like the QM. Building these boxes is your passion, and it is appreciated. Don&#39;t let the ramblings of other folks keep you from doing that which you love. Anyone can tell you are passionate about your work, and you just keep refining your designs. Good things are coming in that regard.

Sorry I will get off my soapbox now.


Andy



